# Volume-Weighted TEMA (VW-TEMA) Indicator â€“ Pine Script v5 Specification

## Purpose
Create a TradingView Pine Script v6 indicator that calculates and plots a **Volumeâ€‘Weighted Triple Exponential Moving Average (VWâ€‘TEMA)**, optionally including the EVWAP base series and Standard devistion ATR bands.

## Inputs
- length: int (default 50)
- src: price source (default close)
- showEvwap: bool (default true)
- showBands: bool (default true)
- atrLen: int (default 14)
- atrMult: float (default 1.0)
- lineWidth: int (default 2)

## Calculations
### EVWAP
- pvEma = EMA(src * volume, length)
- vEma  = EMA(volume, length)
- evwap = pvEma / vEma

### TEMA of EVWAP
- e1 = EMA(evwap, length)
- e2 = EMA(e1, length)
- e3 = EMA(e2, length)
- vwtema = 3*e1 - 3*e2 + e3

### ATR Bands (optional)
- atrValue  = ATR(atrLen)
- upperBand = vwtema + atrMult * atrValue
- lowerBand = vwtema - atrMult * atrValue

## Plotting Requirements
- Pine v6, overlay = true
- Plot VW-TEMA (linewidth = lineWidth)
- Plot EVWAP only if showEvwap = true
- Plot ATR bands only if showBands = true
- Fill between upper/lower ATR bands

## Output
A complete Pine Script v6 implementation exactly following this specification.